						<div class="postbody">&quot;8:7&quot; is probably the <em>pixel</em> aspect ratio: each pixel is 14% wider than it is tall. When multiplied by the number of pixels in the conventionally visible portion of the NES picture (256x224), this produces 64:49, or close to 4:3 <em>display</em> aspect ratio.</div>

