						<div class="postbody">Yes, these 24 pixels are what the PPU outputs during what Rec. 601 considers the active picture period. Most are indeed the color in $3F00, but I seem to remember reading that the first is actually gray in order to give some TVs a better idea of where the picture begins even if $3F00 is black.</div>

